<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.199/43: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in
                            France</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-14T18:00:00-05:00">October 14, 1937—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>B–352. Your 380, October 13, 3 p.m. In view of circumstances reported no
                            further effort should be made for Chapman to visit Spanish territory to
                            investigate Zabala case.</p>
                        <p>We are awaiting report from Consul at Seville before taking further
                            action with regard to reopening of Consulate at Bilbao. In the meantime
                            no further action should be taken by you in this regard.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>